---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Phone Repair FAQ Dallas Fort Worth | Common Questions | GadgetFix"
  description="Answers to common questions about phone repair in Dallas Fort Worth. Repair times, warranty, service areas, and more. Mobile repair service available."
  keywords="phone repair questions, iphone repair time, samsung repair warranty, mobile repair service dallas"
>
  <main class="faq-page">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Frequently Asked Questions - Phone Repair Dallas Fort Worth</h1>
      
      <div class="faq-intro">
        <p>Get answers to common questions about our mobile device repair services in the Dallas-Fort Worth area. 
        Can't find your answer? Call us at <a href="tel:4024166942">(402) 416-6942</a>.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-grid">
        <!-- Service FAQs -->
        <section class="faq-section">
          <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-icon">
              <svg role="img" aria-label="Service and repair icon" width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M14.7 6.3a1 1 0 0 0 0 1.4l1.6 1.6a1 1 0 0 0 1.4 0l3.77-3.77a6 6 0 0 1-7.94 7.94l-6.91 6.91a2.12 2.12 0 0 1-3-3l6.91-6.91a6 6 0 0 1 7.94-7.94l-3.76 3.76z"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h2>Service & Repair Questions</h2>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>How long does screen replacement take?</h3>
            <p>Most <a href="/screen-replacement" style="color: #0066cc; text-decoration: underline;">screen replacements</a> take 30 minutes or less. <a href="/iphone-repair-dallas" style="color: #0066cc; text-decoration: underline;">iPhone screens</a> typically take 25-30 minutes, 
            <a href="/samsung-repair-fort-worth" style="color: #0066cc; text-decoration: underline;">Samsung Galaxy repairs</a> take 30-35 minutes, and iPad screens take 45-60 minutes. We complete repairs 
            on-site while you wait, whether at your home, office, or preferred location in DFW.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Do you come to my location?</h3>
            <p>Yes! We're a 100% mobile repair service covering all of Dallas-Fort Worth. We come to your home, 
            office, coffee shop, or any safe public location. Our service area includes <a href="/locations/dallas-county/dallas" style="color: #0066cc; text-decoration: underline;">Dallas</a>, <a href="/locations/tarrant-county/fort-worth" style="color: #0066cc; text-decoration: underline;">Fort Worth</a>, <a href="/locations/dallas-county/plano" style="color: #0066cc; text-decoration: underline;">Plano</a>, 
            <a href="/locations/collin-county/frisco" style="color: #0066cc; text-decoration: underline;">Frisco</a>, <a href="/locations/dallas-county/irving" style="color: #0066cc; text-decoration: underline;">Irving</a>, <a href="/locations/tarrant-county/arlington" style="color: #0066cc; text-decoration: underline;">Arlington</a>, and surrounding cities within a 30-mile radius.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What areas do you serve?</h3>
            <p>We serve the entire Dallas-Fort Worth metroplex including: <a href="/locations/dallas-county" style="color: #0066cc; text-decoration: underline;">Dallas County</a> (Dallas, Richardson, Garland), 
            <a href="/locations/tarrant-county" style="color: #0066cc; text-decoration: underline;">Tarrant County</a> (Fort Worth, Arlington, Grand Prairie), <a href="/locations/collin-county" style="color: #0066cc; text-decoration: underline;">Collin County</a> (Plano, Frisco, McKinney, Allen), 
            and <a href="/locations/denton-county" style="color: #0066cc; text-decoration: underline;">Denton County</a> (Denton, Lewisville, Flower Mound). Typical arrival time is 30 minutes.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Do you repair water damaged phones?</h3>
            <p>Yes, we offer water damage recovery services with a 70% success rate. Time is critical - the sooner 
            we can disassemble and dry your device, the better the chances. Water damage repair includes full diagnostic, 
            cleaning, and component testing. We serve <a href="/emergency-phone-repair" style="color: #0066cc; text-decoration: underline;">emergency water damage</a> cases throughout Dallas-Fort Worth.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Do you provide free estimates?</h3>
            <p>Yes, we provide FREE diagnostics and estimates for all devices. If your phone won't turn on or has unknown issues, 
            we'll diagnose it at no charge and provide a repair quote. You only pay if you approve the repair. Call us for an instant quote over the phone.</p>
          </div>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Warranty FAQs -->
        <section class="faq-section">
          <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-icon">
              <svg role="img" aria-label="Warranty and quality icon" width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/>
                <path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h2>Warranty & Quality Questions</h2>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What warranty do you offer?</h3>
            <p>All repairs come with our 90-day warranty covering parts and labor. If you experience any issues 
            with the repaired component within 90 days, we'll fix it free of charge. The warranty covers defects 
            but not new damage from drops or water exposure.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Do you use quality parts?</h3>
            <p>We use high-quality parts that meet or exceed manufacturer specifications. These parts 
            offer the same functionality and appearance as original parts with excellent durability. We stand behind 
            our parts with our 90-day warranty.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Will I lose my data during repair?</h3>
            <p>No, screen replacements and most common repairs don't affect your data. Your photos, contacts, apps, 
            and settings remain intact. For water damage or motherboard issues, we always attempt data recovery first. 
            We recommend backing up your device before any repair as a precaution.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Are your technicians certified?</h3>
            <p>Yes, our technicians are experienced professionals with extensive training in mobile device repair. 
            They stay updated on the latest repair techniques for new device models and use professional-grade tools 
            to ensure quality repairs.</p>
          </div>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Device-Specific FAQs -->
        <section class="faq-section">
          <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-icon">
              <svg role="img" aria-label="Device specific icon" width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <rect x="5" y="2" width="14" height="20" rx="2" ry="2"/>
                <line x1="12" y1="18" x2="12.01" y2="18"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h2>Device-Specific Questions</h2>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Can you fix Face ID after screen replacement?</h3>
            <p>Yes, our technicians are trained to preserve Face ID functionality during <a href="/iphone-repair-dallas" style="color: #0066cc; text-decoration: underline;">iPhone screen replacement</a>. 
            We carefully transfer the original components required for Face ID. In rare cases where Face ID doesn't work 
            after repair, we work to resolve the issue or provide alternative solutions.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Do you repair Samsung Z Fold and Z Flip phones?</h3>
            <p>Yes, we specialize in <a href="/samsung-repair-fort-worth" style="color: #0066cc; text-decoration: underline;">Samsung foldable phone repairs</a> including the Z Fold 5, Z Flip 5, and earlier models. 
            These repairs require specialized expertise which our technicians possess. Foldable screen repairs typically 
            take about 45 minutes.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Which iPhone models do you repair?</h3>
            <p>We repair all <a href="/iphone-repair-dallas" style="color: #0066cc; text-decoration: underline;">iPhone models</a> from iPhone 6 through the latest iPhone 15 Pro Max. This includes all 
            standard, Plus, Pro, and Pro Max variants. We also repair iPhone SE models. Common repairs include screen 
            replacement, battery replacement, charging port repair, and camera fixes.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Do you repair tablets and iPads?</h3>
            <p>Yes, we repair all iPad models including iPad Pro, iPad Air, iPad Mini, and standard iPads. 
            Common repairs include <a href="/screen-replacement" style="color: #0066cc; text-decoration: underline;">screen replacement</a>, battery replacement, and charging port repairs. We also 
            service Samsung Galaxy Tabs and other Android tablets.</p>
          </div>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Booking FAQs -->
        <section class="faq-section">
          <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-icon">
              <svg role="img" aria-label="Booking and scheduling icon" width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <rect x="3" y="4" width="18" height="18" rx="2" ry="2"/>
                <line x1="16" y1="2" x2="16" y2="6"/>
                <line x1="8" y1="2" x2="8" y2="6"/>
                <line x1="3" y1="10" x2="21" y2="10"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h2>Booking & Scheduling Questions</h2>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Are you open on weekends?</h3>
            <p>Yes, we're open 7 days a week including weekends. Our hours are Monday through Sunday, 8:00 AM to 6:00 PM. 
            Weekend appointments fill quickly, so we recommend calling early to schedule your preferred time.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Do you offer emergency repair service?</h3>
            <p>Yes, we offer <a href="/emergency-phone-repair" style="color: #0066cc; text-decoration: underline;">emergency same-day repair service</a> throughout Dallas-Fort Worth. For urgent repairs, 
            we typically arrive within 30 minutes to 1 hour. Emergency service is available for all device types. 
            Call <a href="tel:4024166942">(402) 416-6942</a> for immediate assistance.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>How do I schedule a repair?</h3>
            <p>Simply call us at <a href="tel:4024166942">(402) 416-6942</a> to schedule. We'll ask for your device model, 
            the issue, and your preferred location and time. We'll provide a quote over the phone and can often 
            come the same day. You can also visit our <a href="/contact" style="color: #0066cc; text-decoration: underline;">contact page</a> for more information.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What should I do before the technician arrives?</h3>
            <p>Back up your device if possible, note your passcode (we'll need it for testing), and choose a safe 
            location for the repair. If meeting in public, pick a well-lit area like a coffee shop. Have your device 
            ready and remove any case for faster service.</p>
          </div>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Process FAQs -->
        <section class="faq-section">
          <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-icon">
              <svg role="img" aria-label="Repair process icon" width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="m12 19 7-7 3 3-7 7-3-3z"/>
                <path d="m18 13 3-3-3-3-3 3 3 3z"/>
                <path d="m2 6 3-3 3 3-3 3-3-3z"/>
                <path d="M9 10h1l6-6-1-1-6 6v1z"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h2>Repair Process Questions</h2>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What happens during a mobile repair?</h3>
            <p>Our technician arrives at your location with all necessary tools and parts. They'll diagnose your device, 
            confirm the issue and quote, complete the repair while you wait, test all functions, and clean your device. 
            The entire process typically takes 30 minutes for most repairs.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Is mobile repair as good as shop repair?</h3>
            <p>Yes! We bring professional-grade tools and parts to your location. Our mobile setup is complete with 
            everything needed for quality repairs. The only difference is convenience - you don't have to drive anywhere 
            or wait in a shop.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What if the repair takes longer than expected?</h3>
            <p>If we discover additional issues during repair, we'll explain the situation and provide options. 
            You're never obligated to proceed with additional repairs. Most repairs are completed within the estimated 
            time frame.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What payment methods do you accept?</h3>
            <p>We accept cash, all major credit cards, debit cards, and mobile payment apps. Payment is due when 
            the repair is completed. We provide receipts for your records and warranty documentation.</p>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
      
      <div class="cta-section">
        <h2>Still Have Questions?</h2>
        <p>We're here to help! Call us for immediate answers or to schedule your repair.</p>
        <a href="tel:4024166942" class="cta-button">
          <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" style="margin-right: 8px;">
            <path d="M22 16.92v3a2 2 0 0 1-2.18 2 19.79 19.79 0 0 1-8.63-3.07 19.5 19.5 0 0 1-6-6 19.79 19.79 0 0 1-3.07-8.67A2 2 0 0 1 4.11 2h3a2 2 0 0 1 2 1.72 12.84 12.84 0 0 0 .7 2.81 2 2 0 0 1-.45 2.11L8.09 9.91a16 16 0 0 0 6 6l1.27-1.27a2 2 0 0 1 2.11-.45 12.84 12.84 0 0 0 2.81.7A2 2 0 0 1 22 16.92z"/>
          </svg>
          Call Now: (402) 416-6942
        </a>
        <p class="service-note">Mobile Repair Service • 7 Days a Week • 8AM-6PM</p>
        <p class="additional-info">Learn more about <a href="/services" style="color: #0066cc;">our services</a> or <a href="/about" style="color: #0066cc;">about our company</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
.faq-page {
  padding: 2rem 0;
}

